//! The status command should be mostly useful for quick summaries, for example, to check the current modules to-be scanned, and the counter of each rule level warns, as well as other useful quick information. It should exit cleanly always, as it's meant to be used for status view. Here is specially important to parse the manifest and the build system script (specifically and all to whatever it depends or imports) as it's the main responsible for adding and creating modules, which are the entry points for Zig projects.
